  "text": "Compared with other proteins, soy protein has been extensively investigated for the development of biodegradable films due to its abundance, low cost, biodegradability, and biocompatibility [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Soy protein isolate (SPI) is a mixture of proteins containing approximately 90% globulins. 7S and 11S, which amount to about 37% and 31% of major globulins of SPI, have good film-forming ability and",
